Fix the checkstyle errors (complaints about statement on one line).

The extant findbugs red line is about what is there currently it seems. Later says findbugs 'passes'.

Not sure about the javac warnings (was 25 and now is 25).

We just build hbase-common? If so, nice (Thats where changes happened).

Sean Busbey if you looking out...

Not sure about the javac warnings (was 25 and now is 25).

might be YETUS-187, or a variant of YETUS-270.

We just build hbase-common? If so, nice (Thats where changes happened).

Yeah, Yetus only checks modules that have changed unless the project personality tells it otherwise.

return ByteBufferUtils.compareTo(((ByteBufferedCell)left).getFamilyByteBuffer(),

179	          ((ByteBufferedCell)left).getFamilyPosition(), left.getFamilyLength(),

180	          right.getFamilyArray(), right.getFamilyOffset(), right.getFamilyLength());

here right is a BBCell and left is normal Cell. So we should be calling getXXXByteBuffer() method on right and getXXXArray() method on left and here it is just reverse. Not correct for the performance reasons.

To avoid the negation, we should add method in BBUtil
compareTo(byte[] buf1, int o1, int l1, ByteBuffer buf2, int o2, int l2)

We already have compareTo(ByteBuffer buf1, int o1, int l1, byte[] buf2, int o2, int l2)
Thank you for the review Anoop Sam John Let me fix.
Address the good find by Anoop Sam John. The checkstyle complaint is odd Mr Sean Busbey; the problems are addressed by this patch... could it be showing a stale checkstyle report.
If those three checkstyle errors are removed by the patch, that sounds like a bug with how Yetus is calculating diffs.
